subparagraph.text:
processing aids
				that are present by reason of having been added to a cosmetic during the
				processing of such cosmetic;

substances that
				are present by reason of having been added to a cosmetic during processing for
				their technical or functional effect;

compile, maintain,
				and update as appropriate, a list of establishments that are registered under
				this section;

the establishment
				fails to notify the Secretary of changes required under
				subsection (b)(2);

contains
				penetration enhancers, sensitizers, estrogenic chemicals, or other similar
				ingredients;

paragraph.text:
combinations of
				ingredients that may create contaminants of concern when such ingredients
				interact;

the ingredient
				list as it appears on the cosmetic label or insert, including the particle size
				range of any nanoscale cosmetic ingredients;

to prohibit or restrict an ingredient for
				use in cosmetics and list such ingredient on the list under
				section 616(b);

to remove an ingredient from the list of
				ingredients that are safe without limits under
				section 616(c);

was brought to market by a brand
				owner that failed to register and pay the applicable fee as required under
				section 612;
